    "summary": "Mr. Pastor has accumulated over 30 years of professional experience out of which 12 years in Egypt, Burundi and Yemen and more than 15 years in the Netherlands. He was very much involved in water management related aspects in Egypt. He was involved in introducing the first steps of the Water Board concept in Egypt. During the past 20 years he has been working in the Netherlands and has updated his knowledge and experience under the Dutch conditions. \n\nHe is the initiator behind the established Water Operators Partnership (WOP) between the Egyptian and Dutch water authorities. During 2010 - 2016 he had been the representative of the Dutch Water Authorities (DWA)  for the cooperation with the Egyptian water authorities.\n\nHis experience includes project and program management at various levels (team leadership, project manager,  project leader and project advisor), in different fields of expertise within water management (policy making, strategic planning, implementation) and providing at these fields the required technical, organizational and the institutional support. \n\nSpecialties: project and program management, team leader, water management",
